# API Routes & Database Patterns

## Authentication Middleware
All API routes must use consistent auth checking:

```typescript
import { auth } from '@/app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route'
import { getUserRole } from '@/lib/permissions'

export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const session = await auth()
  if (!session?.user?.id) {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 })
  }
  
  // Role-based access control
  const userRole = getUserRole(session.user?.email)
  if (userRole !== 'admin' && userRole !== 'teacher') {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Forbidden' }, { status: 403 })
  }
}
```

## Database Patterns

### Supabase Client Usage
```typescript
import { supabase } from '@/lib/supabase'

// Always handle errors
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('question_bank')
  .select('*')
  .eq('unit_id', unitId)

if (error) {
  console.error('Database error:', error)
  return NextResponse.json({ error: error.message }, { status: 500 })
}
```

### JSONB Storage Pattern
For flexible data storage, use JSONB fields:
```typescript
const questionData = {
  question_data: body.question,          // Full Question object
  question_text: body.question.question, // Extracted for search
  question_type: body.question.type,     // Extracted for filtering
  unit_id: body.unit_id,
  lesson_id: body.lesson_id,
  created_by: session.user.id
}
```

## Error Handling Standards

### Consistent Error Responses
```typescript
// Standardized error format
return NextResponse.json(
  { error: 'Descriptive error message' }, 
  { status: 400 }
)

// Always log errors with context
console.error('Context for debugging:', error)
```

### Try-Catch Blocks
Wrap all database operations:
```typescript
try {
  const { data, error } = await supabase
    .from('table_name')
    .insert(insertData)
    
  if (error) throw error
  
  return NextResponse.json({ data })
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Operation failed:', error)
  return NextResponse.json(
    { error: 'Internal server error' }, 
    { status: 500 }
  )
}
```

